41. Explain your final year project
Answer Structure

Problem → Technology → Your role → Outcome

Example Answer:

“My final year project focuses on solving a real-world problem using software technologies. We designed the system architecture and implemented the main features. My role was mainly in coding, testing, and debugging. This project helped me understand practical application of concepts and teamwork.”

42. What technologies have you used?
Answer Structure

Technology → Where used → Purpose

Example Answer:

“I have used Java, C++, Python, and basic HTML. I used these technologies in academic projects and practice programs to strengthen my fundamentals and problem-solving skills.”

43. What challenges did you face in your project?
Answer Structure

Challenge → Action → Learning

Example Answer:

“One challenge was understanding requirements clearly at the beginning. I overcame this by researching, discussing with my teammates, and breaking the work into smaller tasks. This improved my planning skills.”

44. What did you learn from your project?
Answer Structure

Technical learning → Soft skills

Example Answer:

“I learned how to apply programming concepts practically, debug errors, and work efficiently in a team. It also improved my communication and time management skills.”

45. Explain a technical concept you know
Answer Structure

Concept → Simple definition → Example

Example Answer:

“One technical concept I understand is Object-Oriented Programming. It is a programming approach based on objects and classes. For example, in Java, we use classes to define objects, which helps in code reusability and maintainability.”
